after getting my HoH flag, and the patch supposedly removing the summoning nerf there, I decided to go give that zone a shot. I have not yet found any mobs that can be single pulled, so I started off with the two that came when I tried, heh. Grouped them up a bit and snared them, then proceeded to Pillar of Flame them. It became clear quickly that I was going to run out of mana before they ran out of hp. This is nothing new to me, I just haven't learned how to deal with it yet on more than one mob. With singles it is easy enough to just root and med, but what do you guys do when you have 4? Even our more advanced root spells don't seem reliable enough to me to park 4 mobs, and even if it was they would get spread out again, so that can't be it.<br>
I did some searching, but the keywords I chose didnt come up with anything. I read Graffe's guide. <br>
So I am wondering if maybe my gear is simply insufficient? I have basically a full set of HoT gear, a Mana Preservation 3 item, an ID3 item (which doesnt work on Pillars I know), FT4, SCM2, the lvl 60 Familiar, and a mana pool of about 4k before buffs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 2:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding mobs with more hp than you have mana</span><hr size=1> There was a post back in the arcanist hall that outlined HoH quadding qite well, Baisically with your setup the poster would have suggested (I imagine) Get VoQ get PoTN get Kitty if available then use a horse (has to be the good ones) basically its gettting manaregen so that the time it takes you to run around and cast you med back most of what it takes to nuke. the horse is imparative. If you cant quad them yet (there is no parking just running like a fool while you wait for mana to regen, a highlight of med quadding i guess) try PoStorms frogs single, might have to med kite on them but they are single.....<br>
<br>
 Basically you NEED the horse or lots and lots of manaregen, PoFire quadding (as i hear it told still a bit til i get there hehe) could be done with 1k manapools, seeing as you dont go below 80m due to insane manaregen.<br>
<br>
